@startuml
skinparam shadowing false
title Personality OS - Month One Delivery Organization

rectangle "Founder / Product Ops" as Ops
rectangle "OS / Boot Lead" as Boot
rectangle "Runtime Lead" as Runtime
rectangle "Policy / Systems Lead" as Policy

rectangle "Week 1\nBoot Path" as W1
rectangle "Week 2\nRuntime & Memory" as W2
rectangle "Week 3\nPolicy & Events" as W3
rectangle "Week 4\nHardening & Demo" as W4

artifact "Bootable QEMU Image" as Image
artifact "Scripted Demo Flow" as Demo
artifact "Proof Artifacts" as Proof

Ops --> Boot : acceptance gates\nand daily integration
Ops --> Runtime : demo UX\nand operator flow
Ops --> Policy : command surface\nand proof criteria

Boot --> W1 : own
Runtime --> W2 : own
Policy --> W3 : own
Ops --> W4 : drive integration

W1 --> Image : initramfs,\nPID1, boot chain
W2 --> Image : shell, identity,\nmemory basics
W3 --> Image : event adapter,\npolicy broker, audit
W4 --> Demo : repeatable demo
W4 --> Proof : milestone evidence

W1 --> W4 : foundation
W2 --> W4 : integration input
W3 --> W4 : integration input

note bottom of Image
Month-one POC outcome:
- boot into personality-owned session
- mediate bounded OS actions
- preserve guarded or recovery path
end note
@enduml

@startuml
skinparam shadowing false
title Personality OS - Month One Proof Gates

start
:Week 1\nBootable QEMU image;
if (Boot path stable?) then (yes)
  :Week 2\nPersonality owns first session;
else (no)
  stop
endif

if (Session ownership proven?) then (yes)
  :Week 3\nBrokered actions + audit trail;
else (no)
  stop
endif

if (Bounded action mediation proven?) then (yes)
  :Week 4\nFailure path + demo packaging;
else (no)
  stop
endif

if (Repeatable demo on fresh image?) then (yes)
  :Month-one POC complete;
else (no)
  stop
endif
stop
@enduml
